ssing the experiences of global companies, including Nokia, Uber, IBM, and Apple, the authors explore three key themes: declining economic dynamism in Western economies; growing corporate reluctance to contest markets and innovate; and excessive regulation limiting the diffusion of innovation. At a time of low growth, high unemployment, and increasing income inequality, innovation-led growth is more necessary than ever. This book unequivocally details the obstacles hindering our future prosperity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCapitalism. 0aLabor. 0aTechnological innovationsxEconomic aspects. 0aTechnological innovationsxSocial aspects. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Entrepreneurship.2bisacsh1 aWeigel, Björn, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030021740740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030022212840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300222128423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300222128/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY